Figure 2 — SHAKE Monte Carlo Test Range = maxOutBytes - minOutBytes + 1 OutputLen = maxOutBytes For j = 0 to 99 MD[0] = SEED For i = 1 to 1000 MSG[i] = 128 leftmost bits of MD[i-1] if (MSG[i] < 128 bits) Append 0 bits on rightmost side of MSG[i] til MSG[i] is 128 bits MD[i] = SHAKE(M[i], OutputLen * 8)
if (i != 1000) RightmostOutputBits = 16 rightmost bits of MD[i] as an integer OutputLen = minOutBytes + (RightmostOutputBits % Range)
Output MD[1000], OutputLen SEED = MD[1000]
